text: As we combat the Coronavirus, many of us have an opportunity to do a great deal of good, an opportunity to make a difference in our communities.
post_text: As we combat the Coronavirus, many of us have an opportunity to do a great deal of good, an opportunity to make a difference in our communities.

text:
While in district this week Susan and I are supporting a local small business every day. Today, it was the Original Chop House Burgers, 2502 Little Rd., in Arlington. Owner Kenny Mills worked up one of the best meals we ever had. We picked up some great burgers and fries, as well as a King Ranch Casserole for later. This place gets 5 stars from the Wrights! I encourage everybody to support our local small businesses during the COVID-19 emergency, including take out orders from restaurants like Chop House Burgers. Now is the time to support each other! We will get through this!

Thanks to Tom Ware for turning us on to their King Ranch Casserole!
